<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="generally-adv">generally <strong><em>adv</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'dʒenrəli/    美 /'dʒenrəli/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-widely">1.★ <strong>普遍地；广泛地 (widely)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It is <strong>generally accepted</strong> that smoking is harmful to our health.
人们普遍认为吸烟有害健康。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-usually">2.★ <strong>通常 (usually)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>His little daughter generally gets up at six o’clock.
他的小女儿通常6点起床。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>总体上来说：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Generally, I am in favour of the view.
总的来说，我赞成这个看法。</p><footer>2014 江苏书面表达改</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="generally-speaking">generally speaking</h3>
<p>1.<strong>一般说来：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Generally speaking, the more you pay, the more you get.
一般来说，付出的越多，得到的越多。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li><strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (一般来说), the more expensive the camera, the better its quality.  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. Generally speaking / In general  </p></div>